00:18:13,692 --> 00:18:15,683
You tell her I want she should
come home for dinner.

215
00:18:15,761 --> 00:18:17,820
<i>Understand?</i>
Sure. I tell her
lotsa time.

216
00:18:17,896 --> 00:18:20,990
"Come home. Come home.
Tony no like."

217
00:18:21,066 --> 00:18:23,125
<i>[Door Slams]</i>
But she don't...

218
00:18:40,085 --> 00:18:42,519
That's a nice way
I catch ya, huh?
What do you mean, "catch me"?

219
00:18:42,588 --> 00:18:44,317
I wasn't doin' nothin'.
You was kissin' him.

220
00:18:44,389 --> 00:18:46,186
Sure. What of it?
Well, I don't like it.

221
00:18:46,258 --> 00:18:48,818
You're missin' lots of fun.
Listen, I don't want anyone
kissin' my sister. Understand?

222
00:18:48,894 --> 00:18:50,885
You're hurtin' my arm!
I don't want anybody
puttin' their hands on you!

223
00:18:50,963 --> 00:18:52,794
What do you think
<i>you're</i> doing?
I'm your brother.

224
00:18:52,865 --> 00:18:55,925
You don't act it.
You act more like...
I don't know.

225
00:18:56,001 --> 00:18:58,765
Sometimes I think...
I don't care what you think.
You do what I say.

226
00:18:58,837 --> 00:19:02,773
Sure, and never have any fun.
Oh, "never have any fun."
You call that fun, huh?

227
00:19:02,841 --> 00:19:05,833
Runnin' around with
guys like that.
That's "fun."

228
00:19:05,911 --> 00:19:07,902
Listen, you want
real fun, huh?

229
00:19:09,148 --> 00:19:12,015
Here. How's that?

230
00:19:14,653 --> 00:19:18,089
Gee, Tony! Where'd you get it?
Never mind where I got it.
You just spend it, see?

231
00:19:18,157 --> 00:19:20,853
<i>Tony, you're swell.</i>

232
00:19:20,926 --> 00:19:22,917
Go on.
Get ready for dinner.

233
00:19:22,995 --> 00:19:25,054
And remember,
you do what I say.

234
00:19:25,130 --> 00:19:27,121
<i>No more fellas,</i>
<i>understand?</i>

235
00:19:28,667 --> 00:19:30,760
What for you wanna
give her money, huh?

236
00:19:30,836 --> 00:19:33,134
Ma, she's just a kid.
She wants to have fun.

237
00:19:33,205 --> 00:19:36,572
Yeah? Sometime,
I think you crazy.

238
00:19:38,911 --> 00:19:41,402
Cesca!

239
00:19:43,649 --> 00:19:46,311
What for you take
that money, huh?
Because I want it. That's why.

240
00:19:46,385 --> 00:19:48,785
Give it back.
It's bad money.

241
00:19:48,854 --> 00:19:52,051
Tony no got it
in no good way. It gonna
bring you lotsa trouble.

242
00:19:52,124 --> 00:19:55,252
What do I care where he gets it?
There's nothing wrong
with his giving it to me.

243
00:19:55,327 --> 00:19:58,455
Tony wants me
to have a good time.
Oh, yes? You listen!

244
00:19:58,530 --> 00:20:01,192
Tony no love you
like he make you believe.

245
00:20:01,266 --> 00:20:03,962
All the time,
he smile on top,

246
00:20:04,036 --> 00:20:07,369
but what he thinks...
Oh, he's got lotsa tricks.

247
00:20:07,439 --> 00:20:10,875
He no give money
to nobody for nothing.
He would to his sister.

248
00:20:10,943 --> 00:20:14,071
Sister. Huh!
That make no difference.

249
00:20:14,146 --> 00:20:16,410
To him, you're just
another girl.

250
00:20:16,481 --> 00:20:19,211
Someday when he need you,
he mix you up
in his business...

251
00:20:19,284 --> 00:20:24,017
just like anyone else,
and he's gonna make you
bad like him.

252
00:20:24,089 --> 00:20:26,080
He can't make me do
anything I don't want to.

253
00:20:26,158 --> 00:20:28,786
I'm gonna live my own life.
I can take care of myself.

254
00:20:28,860 --> 00:20:32,921
Yeah? All the time,
Tony say like that.

255
00:20:34,066 --> 00:20:37,627
Afterward, he no
belong to me no more.

256
00:20:37,703 --> 00:20:39,694
He's-a no good,

257
00:20:39,771 --> 00:20:42,706
and now you start to be
just like him.

258
00:20:42,774 --> 00:20:45,368
No, I'm not.
Don't worry about me.

259
00:20:48,113 --> 00:20:50,104
I'll get along
all right.

260
00:20:55,587 --> 00:20:59,421
<i>[Barrel Organ]</i>

261
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:10,994
[Continues]

262
00:21:18,110 --> 00:21:20,135
Hey.

263
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:23,671
[Stops]

264
00:21:33,258 --> 00:21:35,249
[Starts]

265
00:21:35,327 --> 00:21:37,318
Thank you.
Thank you.

266
00:22:24,543 --> 00:22:27,569
That's all right, boys.
Just changin' the name
on the door.

267
00:22:27,646 --> 00:22:30,945
Meet the new president...
Johnny Lovo.

268
00:22:32,217 --> 00:22:34,208
Hiya, boys.

269
00:22:46,865 --> 00:22:49,663
Where's Berdini,
Zeigler, Meehan?

270
00:22:49,735 --> 00:22:51,726
Anybody see 'em?
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>I did.</i>

271
00:22:51,803 --> 00:22:54,067
They ain't comin'.
<i>[Lovo]</i>
<i>Is that all they said?</i>

272
00:22:54,139 --> 00:22:57,006
- They said you could take a flyin'...
- Okay, okay.

273
00:22:57,075 --> 00:22:59,635
Now we know
where they stand.

274
00:22:59,711 --> 00:23:03,272
All right, you guys,
I'm makin' a speech.
Here it is.

275
00:23:03,348 --> 00:23:05,816
Big Louie gets a wad of dough,
and then he gets soft.

276
00:23:05,884 --> 00:23:08,045
He lets you guys come
into the South Side and run beer.

277
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:10,782
Well, I'm gonna change it, see?
You can still stay in,

278
00:23:10,856 --> 00:23:13,188
<i>but, from now on,</i>
<i>you're operatin'the way I say.</i>

279
00:23:13,258 --> 00:23:15,317
Are you askin' us
or telling us?

280
00:23:15,394 --> 00:23:19,057
I'm tellin' ya.
We're gonna get organized,
and I'm gonna handle the works.

281
00:23:19,131 --> 00:23:22,396
<i>It's gonna mean twice</i>
<i>as much dough for everybody</i>
<i>and half as much trouble.</i>

282
00:23:22,467 --> 00:23:24,992
- You got somethin'
figured out, Johnny?
- Everything.

283
00:23:25,070 --> 00:23:27,436
Not being able to get it's
gonna make this town
thirstier than ever.

284
00:23:27,506 --> 00:23:30,907
Runnin' beer ain't a nickel game
anymore. It's a business. I'm
gonna run it like a business.

285
00:23:30,976 --> 00:23:33,968
Swell. We've been cuttin'
each other's throats
long enough.

286
00:23:34,045 --> 00:23:37,572
There are 3,000 saloons on the
South Side... half a million
customers. Figure that out.

287
00:23:37,649 --> 00:23:41,085
<i>Add up what they're gonna lay</i>
<i>on the line every year for</i>
<i>drinks, and nobody in charge.</i>

288
00:23:41,153 --> 00:23:45,681
- So you're going to be it.
- Yeah, <i>it.</i> That's me.

289
00:23:45,757 --> 00:23:48,885
I make my own beer,
and I got my own trucks.

290
00:23:50,362 --> 00:23:53,763
I don't have to go
into business with nobody.

291
00:23:57,502 --> 00:24:00,494
Where you goin'?
Who wants to know?

292
00:24:05,010 --> 00:24:08,969
You sit down here,
and don't interrupt
the president no more.

293
00:24:14,453 --> 00:24:16,444
All right, President.

294
00:24:18,156 --> 00:24:21,387
Well, are the rest
of you guys in or out?
<i>[Men Chattering Assent]</i>

295
00:24:21,460 --> 00:24:25,988
- What about Meehan?
- Yeah. Berdini and Zeigler?

296
00:24:26,064 --> 00:24:28,965
Why, they been sellin'
to 700, 800 joints
between them.

297
00:24:29,034 --> 00:24:32,663
Yeah? Well,
from now on, they're out.
Those joints buy from us.

298
00:24:32,737 --> 00:24:35,331
Sure. If you try to sell
at one of those places,

299
00:24:35,407 --> 00:24:37,637
Meehan'll turn
this side of the town
into a shootin' gallery.

300
00:24:37,709 --> 00:24:40,075
Fine. Anything he starts,
we'll finish.

301
00:24:40,145 --> 00:24:42,978
You guys don't have to worry.
All you gotta do
is to haul beer.

302
00:24:43,048 --> 00:24:46,916
Yeah? Well, who's gonna
stick his neck in those joints
to get the orders?

303
00:24:46,985 --> 00:24:52,048
- My friend Tony Camonte.
- Yeah. I'm what he call
"a good salesman."

304
00:24:52,123 --> 00:24:54,557
Hey, I start right now
to get orders, hey, boss?

305
00:24:54,626 --> 00:24:57,595
All you can get.
Go to it.
Hey.

306
00:24:57,662 --> 00:24:59,687
Dope, got a pencil?

307
00:25:01,600 --> 00:25:03,591
[Italian Accent]
Oh, boys, I don't write.

308
00:25:08,640 --> 00:25:10,631
That's one.
Come on.

309
00:25:12,677 --> 00:25:14,668
Come on, Little Boy.
Business.

310
00:25:16,014 --> 00:25:18,710
[Chattering]

311
00:25:20,819 --> 00:25:23,344
<i>[Men Chattering]</i>

312
00:25:24,923 --> 00:25:27,357
Here, have your beer.

313
00:25:27,425 --> 00:25:30,588
Hey! What is this?
Let go of me, will ya?

314
00:25:30,662 --> 00:25:32,960
What do ya want?
Let go of me.

315
00:25:33,031 --> 00:25:36,364
Let go!
What's the idea?
Come on.

316
00:25:36,434 --> 00:25:39,062
Say, what's the big idea?
Sit down.

317
00:25:39,137 --> 00:25:41,128
Who you buyin'
your beer from?
Meehan and Berdini.

318
00:25:41,206 --> 00:25:43,197
How many barrels
a day?
Three.

319
00:25:43,275 --> 00:25:45,300
He's lyin', Tony.
He's been takin' five.

320
00:25:45,377 --> 00:25:47,368
Chiseler. Well, you're
gettin' eight now, see?

321
00:25:47,445 --> 00:25:49,436
And you're buyin'
from us... Johnny Lovo.
But, listen...

322
00:25:49,514 --> 00:25:51,675
Sit down.
I can't use eight
barrels around here.

323
00:25:51,750 --> 00:25:53,741
I'll get ya
a hunk of soap.
You take a bath in it.

324
00:25:53,818 --> 00:25:55,809
What are you payin'
a barrel?
Fifty.

325
00:25:55,887 --> 00:25:57,878
Well, ours is 65.
It's better.

326
00:25:57,956 --> 00:26:00,254
You get delivery tomorrow.
What am I gonna tell
Meehan and Berdini?

327
00:26:00,325 --> 00:26:02,987
We'll take care of them.
Don't worry.

328
00:26:03,061 --> 00:26:05,621
Well, that's
order number one.

329
00:26:05,697 --> 00:26:09,724
Now we get plenty more.
There's a system
to these things.

330
00:26:12,671 --> 00:26:15,663
<i>[Tony]</i>
<i>How many barrels</i>
<i>did you say you wanted?</i>

331
00:26:15,740 --> 00:26:17,731
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Six.</i>
<i>[Tony] Yeah?</i>

332
00:26:17,809 --> 00:26:20,676
Well, you're gettin' 10.

333
00:26:20,745 --> 00:26:22,770
You're gettin' a delivery
tomorrow.

334
00:26:28,687 --> 00:26:32,179
There's no use
arguin' with this joint.
Zeigler runs it himself.

335
00:26:33,124 --> 00:26:35,115
[Glass Shatters]
Step on it!

336
00:26:55,480 --> 00:26:58,643
<i>[Gunshots]</i>

337
00:26:59,684 --> 00:27:01,811
<i>[Groaning]</i>
<i>[Gunshots]</i>

338
00:27:01,886 --> 00:27:03,877
<i>[Gunshots]</i>

339
00:27:05,390 --> 00:27:07,381
<i>[Gunshots]</i>

340
00:27:18,536 --> 00:27:20,697
Hi, boss.

341
00:27:20,772 --> 00:27:22,763
[Sniffs]
Mm! Lotsa garlic.

342
00:27:22,841 --> 00:27:24,832
[Italian]
Get me some too.

343
00:27:24,909 --> 00:27:26,900
Well, how's business?
You get some more orders?
Lotsa orders.

344
00:27:26,978 --> 00:27:28,969
They all buy from us.
All we have to do is fill 'em.

345
00:27:29,047 --> 00:27:31,311
Yeah. That's a good idea.
You better tell
Meehan and Berdini.

346
00:27:31,383 --> 00:27:34,375
Oh, them fellas, they
retired from business.
What have you been doin'?

347
00:27:34,452 --> 00:27:37,080
You remember you say all
they have to do is start
something, we finish it?

348
00:27:37,155 --> 00:27:38,986
<i>[Paperboy Shouting]</i>
Well, did ya?

349
00:27:39,057 --> 00:27:41,218
About an hour ago.
Hey! Hey, kid.
Come here.

350
00:27:41,292 --> 00:27:43,920
Extra here!
Hey! Keep the change.

351
00:27:43,995 --> 00:27:46,623
All right. Thanks.
Here you are, boss.

352
00:27:46,698 --> 00:27:50,429
There's your South Side,
all nailed up in a box.
All nailed up in...

353
00:27:50,502 --> 00:27:52,732
Yeah, well, you didn't
get the lid on very tight.
What do you mean?

354
00:27:52,804 --> 00:27:55,568
Look at that.

355
00:28:05,850 --> 00:28:09,013
Come on. Hey, keep this hot.
We'll be back for it.

356
00:28:13,591 --> 00:28:15,582
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>You can't come in here.!</i>
<i>[Tony] Get outta here.!</i>

357
00:28:15,660 --> 00:28:18,151
This is a private
hospital! You can't...
<i>[Muttering]</i>

358
00:28:29,207 --> 00:28:32,142
<i>[Man Screams]</i>
<i>[Gunshots]</i>

359
00:28:33,978 --> 00:28:36,970
[Crying]
Oh!

360
00:28:37,048 --> 00:28:39,141
Oh! What
did they do?

361
00:28:57,335 --> 00:28:59,565
Hiya, Poppy.
Hello.

362
00:28:59,637 --> 00:29:03,733
Hey, what's all the time
bitin' you?
You afraid of me?

363
00:29:03,808 --> 00:29:06,299
Well, that outfit's enough
to give anybody the yips.

364
00:29:06,377 --> 00:29:10,711
Nice, huh?
I got three more...
different colors.

365
00:29:10,782 --> 00:29:14,240
I see you're goin' in
for jewelry. It's kind of
effeminate, isn't it?

366
00:29:14,319 --> 00:29:17,220
Huh? Yeah.
I got 'em at an auction.

367
00:29:17,288 --> 00:29:20,086
A bargain.
[Laughing]

368
00:29:22,093 --> 00:29:24,254
You sure are
a funny mixture, Tony.

369
00:29:24,329 --> 00:29:27,662
That's the first time
you smiled.
Yeah?

370
00:29:27,732 --> 00:29:31,532
Well, how do you mean
you think I'm funny?
You just are. That's all.

371
00:29:31,603 --> 00:29:33,594
What else are you doing
with all your money?

372
00:29:33,671 --> 00:29:36,902
I hear you're gettin'
a new car.
Mm-hmm. It's different.

373
00:29:36,975 --> 00:29:39,307
It's got bullet-proof glass
and a steel body.

374
00:29:39,377 --> 00:29:42,141
And I got myself
a new house too.

375
00:29:42,213 --> 00:29:44,204
Come up sometime?

376
00:29:44,282 --> 00:29:46,944
Yeah. I'll bring
my grandmother.

377
00:29:48,019 --> 00:29:50,010
No kiddin. You come up?

378
00:29:50,088 --> 00:29:52,716
Why don't you get
yourself a girl, Tony?

379
00:29:52,791 --> 00:29:54,782
I'm workin' on that now.

380
00:29:54,859 --> 00:29:58,556
Yeah? Well, don't
tire yourself out.

381
00:30:07,705 --> 00:30:09,696
<i>[Billiard Balls Clicking]</i>

382
00:30:15,747 --> 00:30:17,738
Is Johnny in?
Yeah.

383
00:30:17,816 --> 00:30:19,807
He's mad, huh?

384
00:30:28,760 --> 00:30:31,024
Hiya, boss.

385
00:30:31,095 --> 00:30:34,030
When are you gonna learn
that I am the boss?
Sure, you're the boss.

386
00:30:34,098 --> 00:30:36,259
Then what do you mean
by breaking up that
Lakeview joint last night?

387
00:30:36,334 --> 00:30:39,303
Didn't I tell you to stay
out of the North Side?
Listen, Johnny, it was easy.

388
00:30:39,370 --> 00:30:42,339
You listen to me, stupid.
That was one of O'Hara's
places, and you know it.

389
00:30:42,407 --> 00:30:44,432
Didn't I tell you
I wasn't ready
for O'Hara yet?

390
00:30:44,509 --> 00:30:48,468
It was a nice little order...
50 barrels a week.
I don't care if it's 50 a day.

391
00:30:48,546 --> 00:30:50,537
What do you use
to think with,
an empty beer keg?

392
00:30:50,615 --> 00:30:52,606
Just when we get
this territory lined up
and runnin' smooth,

393
00:30:52,684 --> 00:30:54,777
you step out
and gum up the parade.
How do you mean, Johnny?

394
00:30:54,853 --> 00:30:57,754
I just sell
a little more beer.
Aw, don't worry.

395
00:30:57,822 --> 00:31:00,086
Don't worry?
You know what O'Hara's
liable to do now?

396
00:31:00,158 --> 00:31:02,718
He'll send his guns down here
on the South Side. They'll
move around like hummingbirds.

397
00:31:02,794 --> 00:31:05,627
You're liable to get it,
and I'm liable to get it.
He's tough.

398
00:31:05,697 --> 00:31:10,031
Aw, he ain't so tough...
hangin' out in a flower shop.

399
00:31:10,101 --> 00:31:14,697
- You afraid of a guy like that?
- I ain't afraid of anybody.

400
00:31:14,772 --> 00:31:16,865
Sure, you're not.

401
00:31:17,909 --> 00:31:20,639
That's a crazy question,
hey, Johnny?

402
00:31:20,712 --> 00:31:23,510
Come on. Don't argue.
Where you goin'?

403
00:31:23,581 --> 00:31:27,039
To clean up after you, you mug,
unless it's too late.

404
00:31:27,118 --> 00:31:29,109
<i>[Billiard Balls Clicking]</i>

405
00:31:44,636 --> 00:31:46,627
Look out!

406
00:31:56,147 --> 00:31:59,548
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>It's Keach.</i>
[All Chattering]

407
00:32:04,555 --> 00:32:06,546
[Chattering]

408
00:32:21,806 --> 00:32:24,866
<i>[Phone Rings]</i>

409
00:32:30,181 --> 00:32:32,342
Hello. Hello?

410
00:32:33,952 --> 00:32:36,716
Hel... Hello.

411
00:32:36,788 --> 00:32:39,256
Hello. This Mr. Camonte's
secretary.

412
00:32:39,324 --> 00:32:43,385
What's the name, please?
This Mr. Camonte's
secretary.

413
00:32:43,461 --> 00:32:46,453
<i>Secretary, I told you.</i>
Hey, hey, hey.

414
00:32:46,531 --> 00:32:49,694
<i>Secretary,</i> you dope.
<i>Secretary.</i>

415
00:32:50,969 --> 00:32:54,405
Oh. Okay, boss.

416
00:32:54,472 --> 00:32:58,374
No, no. I no talkin' on you. I was
talkin' on Mr. Camonte. That's my boss.

417
00:32:58,443 --> 00:33:00,604
That's...
Hey, hey.
Get a name.

418
00:33:00,678 --> 00:33:02,669
Get a name.

419
00:33:02,747 --> 00:33:05,648
What's your name?

420
00:33:05,717 --> 00:33:08,242
No, no. I don't wanna know
what's your brother's name.

421
00:33:08,319 --> 00:33:11,618
I wanna know
what's <i>your</i> name.

422
00:33:11,689 --> 00:33:15,625
Oh, you do, huh?
Listen, I come on over there,
I smack you right in the teeth.

423
00:33:15,693 --> 00:33:17,923
I get you, your brother...
Hey! What's-a matter?

424
00:33:17,996 --> 00:33:20,658
That's no way to talk.
Talk nice.

425
00:33:20,732 --> 00:33:23,257
Tell him to state
his business.

426
