<i>it's Valentine's Day?</i>
<i>Oh, yeah. I forgot.</i>

645
00:48:21,598 --> 00:48:23,725
<i>Come on.</i>
<i>Line up, you guys.</i>

646
00:48:23,800 --> 00:48:26,030
<i>Over there,</i>
<i>all seven of you.</i>

647
00:48:26,103 --> 00:48:28,697
<i>What's the gag?</i>
<i>Is the heat on?</i>

648
00:48:28,772 --> 00:48:31,639
<i>Plenty.</i>
<i>Face the wall.!</i>

649
00:48:33,310 --> 00:48:36,768
<i>Put your mitts up.</i>
<i>All of you.!</i>

650
00:48:36,847 --> 00:48:39,748
<i>[Gunfire]</i>

651
00:48:42,085 --> 00:48:44,451
<i>[Dog Whimpering]</i>

652
00:48:44,521 --> 00:48:47,513
<i>[Dog Barking]</i>

653
00:48:57,601 --> 00:49:02,300
Here's Gaffney.
Gaffney, what do you
know about this? Well?

654
00:49:02,372 --> 00:49:05,500
Well, I was on my way
here to the garage
to keep an appointment.

655
00:49:05,575 --> 00:49:07,509
I was late.
Yeah?

656
00:49:07,577 --> 00:49:10,444
And a car drives up
and some guys pile out.

657
00:49:10,514 --> 00:49:13,483
Two of'em was cops...
at least they was dressed
like cops.

658
00:49:13,550 --> 00:49:15,950
Cops. That's a new gag.
Then what?

659
00:49:16,019 --> 00:49:19,955
Well, it looked like a pinch,
so I beat it around the block.
Then he picked me up.

660
00:49:20,023 --> 00:49:23,959
Yeah, lucky you were late.
Now take a good peek
and see what you missed.

661
00:49:24,027 --> 00:49:26,393
[Man]
Gangway here.
Keep it clear.

662
00:49:47,718 --> 00:49:50,983
Seven of'em...
lined up against a wall.

663
00:49:51,054 --> 00:49:54,182
Mowed down,
just like that!

664
00:49:56,326 --> 00:50:00,023
Didn't have a chance!
Sit down, Chief.
You're wearin' out the carpet.

665
00:50:00,097 --> 00:50:03,032
Yeah? I'm
the only one left.

666
00:50:06,770 --> 00:50:11,207
Thinks he'll get me, huh?
Fat chance!

667
00:50:11,274 --> 00:50:14,038
<i>[Knocking]</i>

668
00:50:15,345 --> 00:50:18,109
Who's there?
<i>McArthur,</i>
<i>from the</i> Journal.

669
00:50:18,181 --> 00:50:20,115
Let him in.

670
00:50:23,854 --> 00:50:26,186
Hi, Gaffney.
How'd you find me?

671
00:50:26,256 --> 00:50:28,520
Oh, we boys from the <i>Journal</i>
always get around.

672
00:50:28,592 --> 00:50:31,720
Yeah? Anybody else
know I'm here?
Nope. Just my own idea.

673
00:50:31,795 --> 00:50:36,391
Sit down. You're
gonna stay for a while.

674
00:50:44,307 --> 00:50:46,935
Well?
Can't get a thing on him.

675
00:50:47,010 --> 00:50:49,501
We're right up a blind alley
wherever we go.

676
00:50:49,579 --> 00:50:52,514
And Gaffney's turned yellow.
He's hiding out.
What about Lovo?

677
00:50:52,582 --> 00:50:55,449
Lovo is practically out.
He's as scared as Gaffney.

678
00:50:55,519 --> 00:50:58,249
It's Camonte, all right,
but we can't prove it yet.
No, but we will.

679
00:50:58,321 --> 00:51:00,255
Hey, Chief.
What do you want?

680
00:51:00,323 --> 00:51:02,188
This fellow Camonte.
What about him?

681
00:51:02,259 --> 00:51:05,057
Public's interested in him.
He's a colorful character.

682
00:51:05,128 --> 00:51:09,155
Colorful? What color
is a crawling louse?

683
00:51:09,232 --> 00:51:12,531
Listen, that's the attitude
of too many morons in this country.

684
00:51:12,602 --> 00:51:15,400
They think these big hoodlums
are some sort of demigods.

685
00:51:15,472 --> 00:51:17,702
What do they do
about a guy like Camonte?

686
00:51:17,774 --> 00:51:20,743
They sentimentalize, romance,
make jokes about him.

687
00:51:20,811 --> 00:51:23,609
They had some excuse for glorifying
our old western bad men.

688
00:51:23,680 --> 00:51:27,616
They met in the middle
of the street at high noon and
waited for each other to draw.

689
00:51:27,684 --> 00:51:30,949
But these things sneak up,
shoot a guy in the back
and then run away.

690
00:51:31,021 --> 00:51:32,955
<i>I guess you're right.</i>
Colorful!

691
00:51:33,023 --> 00:51:37,289
Did you read what happened?
A carful of'em chased another
down the street, broad daylight.

692
00:51:37,360 --> 00:51:41,091
Three kiddies playing hopscotch
get lead poured in their little bellies.

693
00:51:41,164 --> 00:51:44,827
When I think what goes on in the minds
of these lice, I want to vomit.

694
00:51:46,203 --> 00:51:48,137
Ben?
Yeah?

695
00:51:48,205 --> 00:51:51,140
See if you can find Gaffney.
He'll probably get it next.

696
00:51:51,208 --> 00:51:53,768
They got all the others.
Right.

697
00:51:56,279 --> 00:51:59,646
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Our organizations are opposed</i>
<i>to your policy, Mr. Garston.</i>

698
00:51:59,716 --> 00:52:02,446
<i>Your paper could be an influence</i>
<i>against the gangster,</i>

699
00:52:02,519 --> 00:52:05,750
yet you keep right on
playing up his activities
as front-page news.

700
00:52:05,822 --> 00:52:08,586
Murders, gang war, killing!
That's all we read about!

701
00:52:08,658 --> 00:52:10,649
You're glorifying the gangster
by giving him this publicity.

702
00:52:10,727 --> 00:52:15,664
You're trying to tell me
you can get rid of the gangster
by ignoring him?

703
00:52:15,732 --> 00:52:18,997
By keeping him
off the front page?
That's ridiculous!

704
00:52:19,069 --> 00:52:21,003
You're playing
right into his hands!

705
00:52:21,071 --> 00:52:24,563
Show him up! Run him
out of the country! That'll
keep him off the front page.

706
00:52:24,641 --> 00:52:29,340
In the meantime, you expect
our children to read of nothing
but outrage and murder?

707
00:52:29,412 --> 00:52:32,176
That's better than
they're being slaughtered.

708
00:52:32,249 --> 00:52:35,650
The city is full
of machine guns,
gang war in the streets.

709
00:52:35,719 --> 00:52:38,244
Kids aren't even safe
to go to school.

710
00:52:38,321 --> 00:52:41,757
<i>You want that to go on?</i>
Certainly not.

711
00:52:41,825 --> 00:52:43,952
But what can private
citizens do?

712
00:52:44,027 --> 00:52:46,086
Even our police force
can't stop it.

713
00:52:46,163 --> 00:52:48,097
Don't blame the police.

714
00:52:48,165 --> 00:52:52,261
They can't stop machine guns
from being run back and forth
across the state lines.

715
00:52:52,335 --> 00:52:54,735
They can't enforce laws
that don't exist.

716
00:52:54,804 --> 00:52:58,103
Then it's up to
the federal government
to do something about it.

717
00:52:58,175 --> 00:53:00,143
You're the government!
All of you!

718
00:53:00,210 --> 00:53:03,737
Instead of trying to hide
the facts, get laws passed
that'll do some good!

719
00:53:03,813 --> 00:53:06,111
For instance?
Pass a federal law...

720
00:53:06,183 --> 00:53:09,914
that puts the gun
in the same class as drugs
and white slavery!

721
00:53:09,986 --> 00:53:12,546
Put teeth
in the deportation act!

722
00:53:12,622 --> 00:53:15,591
These gangsters
don't belong in this country.
Half of'em aren't citizens!

723
00:53:15,659 --> 00:53:19,720
[Italian Accent]
That's true. They bring nothing
but disgrace to my people.

724
00:53:19,796 --> 00:53:22,959
<i>All right.</i>
<i>I'll tell you what to do.</i>

725
00:53:23,033 --> 00:53:25,524
Make laws and see
that they're obeyed...

726
00:53:25,602 --> 00:53:28,571
if we have to have
martial law to do it!

727
00:53:28,638 --> 00:53:31,869
The governor of New Mexico
declared martial law
to stop a bullfight,

728
00:53:31,942 --> 00:53:35,070
the governor of Oklahoma
to regulate oil production!

729
00:53:35,145 --> 00:53:38,512
Surely gang rule
and wholesale law defiance...

730
00:53:38,582 --> 00:53:40,948
are more of a menace
to the nation...

731
00:53:41,017 --> 00:53:44,282
than the regulation of oil
or a bullfight!

732
00:53:44,354 --> 00:53:47,551
The army will help.
So will the American Legion.

733
00:53:47,624 --> 00:53:50,525
They offered their services
over two years ago!

734
00:53:50,594 --> 00:53:52,960
And nobody
ever called on 'em.

735
00:53:53,029 --> 00:53:57,261
Let's get wise to ourselves.
We're fighting organized murder!

736
00:54:01,071 --> 00:54:04,700
<i>[Applause]</i>

737
00:54:21,224 --> 00:54:24,660
That Sadie Thompson,
she's pretty smart girl.

738
00:54:24,728 --> 00:54:27,663
What's a girl wanna
hustle in a place
like that for?

739
00:54:27,731 --> 00:54:29,926
Yeah, it's
rainin' all the time.

740
00:54:30,000 --> 00:54:32,628
Yeah, that rain.
That's pretty good.

741
00:54:32,702 --> 00:54:35,671
That comes from a pipe,
just like a shower.

742
00:54:35,739 --> 00:54:39,641
Them two fellas...
Which one do you think
she takes?

743
00:54:39,709 --> 00:54:44,203
The guy with the collar?
Nah. He ain't so hot.

744
00:54:44,281 --> 00:54:47,682
Hey, listen. Them marines
ain't so hot too.

745
00:54:47,751 --> 00:54:50,652
[Chuckles]
Come on. I go take a smoke.

746
00:54:50,720 --> 00:54:54,486
[Audience Chattering]

747
00:54:54,557 --> 00:54:57,549
[No Audible Dialogue]

748
00:55:15,879 --> 00:55:19,474
That's a fine show.
I gotta see more
shows like that.

749
00:55:19,549 --> 00:55:21,813
You know, serious.

750
00:55:21,885 --> 00:55:24,877
Ain't got no jokes.
I like a show with jokes.

751
00:55:24,954 --> 00:55:27,752
That's-a dope.
What more do you want?

752
00:55:27,824 --> 00:55:32,523
Listen, this girl Sadie,
she's got what you call
a problem.

753
00:55:32,595 --> 00:55:36,361
This fella with
the collar, he's gonna...

754
00:55:38,635 --> 00:55:41,399
What's the matter?
They found Gaffney.

755
00:55:41,471 --> 00:55:44,304
Spotted him down
at Frank's Bowling Alley.
He got in a game.

756
00:55:44,374 --> 00:55:47,036
Yeah?
It's a setup.
Take about an hour...

757
00:55:47,110 --> 00:55:49,806
I'm lookin' at a show now.
Listen, it's the last act.

758
00:55:49,879 --> 00:55:53,007
There's two fellas after a girl
which is called Sadie, see?

759
00:55:53,083 --> 00:55:57,144
And this girl Sadie,
she's been what you call...
disillusioned.

760
00:55:57,220 --> 00:56:00,155
We gotta do it now!
He's liable
to slip us again.

761
00:56:00,223 --> 00:56:02,953
He's the last one, boss.
Come on, Tony.

762
00:56:04,260 --> 00:56:08,162
Ah, that's too bad.
All right, come on.

763
00:56:08,231 --> 00:56:11,064
Wait a minute.
You stay here.
[Groans]

764
00:56:11,134 --> 00:56:13,625
You stay
and see the show.
Ah, boss!

765
00:56:13,703 --> 00:56:16,570
I gotta know which fella
this girl Sadie, she take.

766
00:56:16,639 --> 00:56:19,802
You stay here and find out,
then come and tell me.

767
00:56:37,494 --> 00:56:39,758
It's all right, boss.
The copper's gone.

768
00:56:39,829 --> 00:56:42,423
All right.
Come on.

769
00:56:42,499 --> 00:56:46,128
Hey, Little Boy,
you go around the back,
up on the balcony.

770
00:56:46,202 --> 00:56:49,660
Hey, Pietro, side door.
He may have friends.
You never can tell.

771
00:56:49,739 --> 00:56:53,004
Joe, I want you to stand
in the alley. If he gets
that far, you do your stuff.

772
00:56:53,076 --> 00:56:55,601
You keep the motor running.
Bring the presents.

773
00:56:55,678 --> 00:56:57,908
You stay here.
Come on, fellas.

774
00:56:57,981 --> 00:57:00,415
Ah, now we'll know what happened
to that girl, Sadie.

775
00:57:00,483 --> 00:57:03,213
Angelo, did she take
the guy with the collar?

776
00:57:03,286 --> 00:57:06,221
Nah. She climb back
in the hay with the army.

777
00:57:06,289 --> 00:57:09,383
Yeah? That's fine.
She's a smart girl, that kid.

778
00:57:09,459 --> 00:57:11,723
Come on.
What're you doin'?

779
00:57:15,532 --> 00:57:18,558
[Whistling]

780
00:57:18,635 --> 00:57:21,570
<i>[Bowling Pins Falling]</i>

781
00:57:37,187 --> 00:57:39,815
Not bad, huh?

782
00:57:39,889 --> 00:57:42,756
[Continues Whistling]

783
00:58:00,743 --> 00:58:03,211
Just watch this one.

784
00:58:08,384 --> 00:58:11,512
<i>[Gunfire]</i>

785
00:58:14,257 --> 00:58:17,124
<i>[Gunfire]</i>

786
00:58:30,740 --> 00:58:33,937
<i>[Jazz]</i>

787
00:58:46,789 --> 00:58:50,020
[Speaking Italian]

788
00:58:52,729 --> 00:58:55,721
<i>Hello, Tony.</i>
How are you?

789
00:58:55,798 --> 00:58:59,393
[Chattering]

790
00:58:59,469 --> 00:59:02,438
Ahhh, that's-a pretty hot!

791
00:59:02,505 --> 00:59:05,235
[Woman]
Hello.
Hello.

792
00:59:12,815 --> 00:59:15,750
Hello.
Hello, stranger.

793
00:59:15,818 --> 00:59:20,653
Chair. Well, Johnny!
Well, you're lookin' swell.

794
00:59:20,723 --> 00:59:23,590
I thought we were gonna
see something of you.

795
00:59:23,660 --> 00:59:27,960
- Well, here I am.
- Where have you been?
On a vacation?

796
00:59:28,031 --> 00:59:32,866
I've been workin'.
Up on the North Side,
huh, Johnny?

797
00:59:32,936 --> 00:59:35,200
That's what the papers say.

798
00:59:35,271 --> 00:59:37,296
Don't work too hard.

799
00:59:37,373 --> 00:59:40,774
<i>I just finish up tonight.</i>
<i>Now I play a while.</i>

800
00:59:52,822 --> 00:59:55,450
You get your own table,
Camonte.

801
00:59:55,525 --> 00:59:58,153
Why is that?
This is a table for two.

802
00:59:58,227 --> 01:00:00,718
Well, maybe you get
another table, huh, Johnny?

803
01:00:00,797 --> 01:00:02,924
Hey, listen, you!
Who do you think you are?

804
01:00:02,999 --> 01:00:06,230
<i>[Gunshots]</i>
[Gasps, Screams]

805
01:00:06,302 --> 01:00:09,169
<i>[Woman Screams]</i>
What are you tryin' to do?

806
01:00:13,810 --> 01:00:15,835
All right, go on.

807
01:00:17,180 --> 01:00:20,115
Nothing seems
to bother you much,
does it?

808
01:00:20,183 --> 01:00:23,584
Well, I get used to noises.

809
01:00:23,653 --> 01:00:26,417
[Indistinct Arguing]

810
01:00:26,489 --> 01:00:29,151
<i>[Man Speaking Italian]</i>

811
01:00:29,225 --> 01:00:31,785
Hello, Guino.
Hello, baby.

812
01:00:34,197 --> 01:00:37,792
Why are you always
high-hatting me?
Go on, beat it.

813
01:00:37,867 --> 01:00:41,200
I suppose you need
an organ grinder to work with?

814
01:00:41,270 --> 01:00:45,001
Tony's inside. He see you
in that outfit?

815
01:00:45,074 --> 01:00:48,168
<i>[Crowd Applauding]</i>
I looked pretty good
from two stories up.

816
01:00:48,244 --> 01:00:51,475
Am I different now?
Wanna dance with me?

817
01:00:51,547 --> 01:00:53,811
Listen, you're
Tony's sister, see?

818
01:00:53,883 --> 01:00:56,545
Besides,
you're only a kid.

819
01:00:56,619 --> 01:00:58,644
I'm 18.

820
01:00:58,721 --> 01:01:02,919
<i>[Ragtime]</i>

821
01:01:19,175 --> 01:01:21,643
You like that music?

822
01:01:26,849 --> 01:01:29,682
Now do you wanna dance?
No.

823
01:01:31,154 --> 01:01:34,612
Afraid! Afraid
ofTony's sister! Why, you...

824
01:01:34,691 --> 01:01:37,819
Well, I notice
you stood there and watched.

825
01:01:39,662 --> 01:01:42,631
Someday you'll find out
you've been missing something.

826
01:01:46,736 --> 01:01:48,897
[No Audible Dialogue]

827
01:01:51,841 --> 01:01:55,868
Hey, how about it,
you and me, huh?

828
01:01:55,945 --> 01:01:57,970
I thought
you weren't dancing.

829
01:01:58,047 --> 01:02:01,039
I changed my mind.
I need exercise.

830
01:02:01,117 --> 01:02:03,483
We show 'em
somethin', huh?

831
01:02:19,969 --> 01:02:22,130
I think you missed me, huh?

832
01:02:22,205 --> 01:02:24,696
That's right.

833
01:02:24,774 --> 01:02:27,675
We make up for lost time.

834
01:02:27,744 --> 01:02:31,009
How do you wanna play,
Tony? Like this?

835
01:02:32,348 --> 01:02:34,282
That's it.

836
01:03:05,348 --> 01:03:08,044
You wait here.
I take her home myself.

837
01:03:08,117 --> 01:03:10,347
You can't!
Shut up!

838
01:03:26,836 --> 01:03:29,031
You'll be sorry for this.

839
01:03:33,276 --> 01:03:37,042
Next time I catch you
in a place like that,
I'm gonna kill you.

840
01:03:37,113 --> 01:03:40,879
You're telling me what
to do? I'll do what I want,
same as you! Understand?

841
01:03:40,950 --> 01:03:43,316
You listen to me!
I hate you!

842
01:03:43,386 --> 01:03:45,980
Never mind what I do!
That's all right.

843
01:03:46,055 --> 01:03:47,989
You're gonna stay home,
understand?

844
01:03:48,057 --> 01:03:50,685
I'm no baby!
I can take care of myself!

845
01:03:50,760 --> 01:03:54,025
Yeah, runnin' around
with the fellas, huh?
Letting 'em hold you like that?

846
01:03:54,096 --> 01:03:57,623
Letting 'em look at you?
Dressin' up like that
for fellas to see, huh?

847
01:03:57,700 --> 01:04:01,158
What I do with fellas
is my business!

848
01:04:02,905 --> 01:04:06,534
<i>[Cesca Screams,</i>
<i>Shouts, Indistinct]</i>

849
01:04:06,609 --> 01:04:10,841
Cesca!
<i>[Sobbing]</i>

850
01:04:12,915 --> 01:04:15,383
Oh, Mama.
Cesca, what's the matter?

851
01:04:15,451 --> 01:04:17,942
What-a Tony do to you, huh?
What he do?

852
01:04:18,020 --> 01:04:21,581
He hit me.
He said he'd kill me,
and I wasn't doing anything.

853
01:04:21,657 --> 01:04:24,820
I was only dancing!
That's all right,
<i>figlia mia.</i> No cry.

854
01:04:24,894 --> 01:04:28,022
All right, tell-a Mama.
Come on upstairs.

855
01:04:28,097 --> 01:04:30,463
No cry, baby.
[Sobbing]

856
01:04:30,533 --> 01:04:34,993
He hasn't any right to.
Just because I'm his sister, he
can't throw me around like that.

857
01:04:35,071 --> 01:04:37,665
All right, no cry, baby.
I tell you.

858
01:04:37,740 --> 01:04:39,799
I tell you lotsa times!

859
01:04:39,876 --> 01:04:43,368
He hurt you! He hurt you!

860
01:04:43,446 --> 01:04:46,210
He hurt everybody.

861
01:04:47,617 --> 01:04:50,085
<i>[Cesca Continues Sobbing]</i>

862
01:04:50,152 --> 01:04:52,518
<i>[Mother]</i>
<i>It's all right.</i>

863
01:05:07,703 --> 01:05:10,194
<i>[Gunfire]</i>

864
01:05:45,207 --> 01:05:47,835
See if you can put out
his tires.
Right.

865
01:05:52,815 --> 01:05:54,442
That got 'er!

866
01:06:04,260 --> 01:06:06,091
Look out!

867
01:06:15,271 --> 01:06:17,705
<i>[Knocking]</i>

868
01:06:19,375 --> 01:06:21,570
<i>[Louder Knocking]</i>

869
01:06:27,516 --> 01:06:30,952
[Speaking Italian]
Just shut up.

870
01:06:31,020 --> 01:06:34,046
Give us some nickels.
Give us some nickels.
Hurry!

871
01:06:39,962 --> 01:06:41,896
[Coin Drops]

872
01:06:41,964 --> 01:06:44,489
Lakeside 1305.

873
01:06:44,567 --> 01:06:46,558
Get me a drink.

874
01:06:47,636 --> 01:06:50,264
[Ringing]

875
01:06:55,177 --> 01:06:58,169
- Hello?
- Hello. Is this Jim?

876
01:06:58,247 --> 01:07:02,047
Tony Camonte.
Is Rinaldo there?

877
01:07:02,118 --> 01:07:04,712
No, Mr. Camonte.
He left an hour ago.

878
01:07:04,787 --> 01:07:06,482
Is Lovo there?

879
01:07:06,555 --> 01:07:08,955
Lovo? No.
He left too.

880
01:07:09,025 --> 01:07:12,085
Said he was going
back to the office.

881
01:07:15,431 --> 01:07:17,365
[Coin Drops]

882
01:07:17,433 --> 01:07:20,231
Bosworth 4503.

883
01:07:24,073 --> 01:07:27,372
<i>[Phone Ringing]</i>

884
01:07:29,245 --> 01:07:33,306
- Hello?
- Hello. Mabel?

885
01:07:33,382 --> 01:07:36,613
Camonte.
Rinaldo there?

886
01:07:36,685 --> 01:07:40,553
Why, no. He ain't been here.
You know, I think that guy's
givin' me the runaround.

887
01:07:40,623 --> 01:07:42,614
I've had a date with him
two or three times...

888
01:07:42,691 --> 01:07:47,253
Maybe he going home to bed.
Ah, what're you talkin'...
That tom cat!

889
01:07:47,329 --> 01:07:49,320
Try Maizie.

890
01:07:49,398 --> 01:07:51,958
Maizie. That's right.
I forgot about her.

891
01:07:52,034 --> 01:07:54,127
[Coin Drops]

892
01:07:54,203 --> 01:07:59,402
Uh... uh, Hatfield 6401.

893
01:08:00,509 --> 01:08:03,535
Yeah, 6401.

894
01:08:05,981 --> 01:08:08,745
[Ringing]

895
01:08:15,324 --> 01:08:18,418
- Come on.
- [Ringing Continues]

896
01:08:22,998 --> 01:08:25,364
- Hello?
- Hello, Maizie?

897
01:08:25,434 --> 01:08:28,733
It's Tony Camonte.
Rinaldo there?

898
01:08:28,804 --> 01:08:30,829
Yeah. For you.

899
01:08:32,708 --> 01:08:35,176
- Hello?
- Hello, Rinaldo?

900
01:08:35,244 --> 01:08:38,372
I'm at Pietro's.
Pietro's!

901
01:08:38,447 --> 01:08:40,813
- Yeah, come right away.
- Anything wrong?

902
01:08:40,883 --> 01:08:42,908
Yeah, plenty.

903
01:08:44,887 --> 01:08:46,912
Go get me a towel.

904
01:08:48,557 --> 01:08:51,526
I thought you weren't
doing anything tonight.

905
01:08:51,594 --> 01:08:53,687
I'll be back later.

906
01:08:55,898 --> 01:08:59,265
This is worse than being
in love with a grasshopper.

907
01:09:08,344 --> 01:09:10,642
<i>[Knocking]</i>

908
01:09:13,782 --> 01:09:16,046
It took you a long time
to get here.

909
01:09:16,118 --> 01:09:19,315
Who done it?
I don't know,
but I got an idea.

910
01:09:19,388 --> 01:09:22,050
You just wait. How
do you stand with Lovo?
Huh?

911
01:09:22,124 --> 01:09:24,786
Come on!
How do you stand
with Lovo?

912
01:09:27,897 --> 01:09:29,831
Who's Lovo?

913
01:09:29,899 --> 01:09:32,561
That's good.
Say when.

914
01:09:32,635 --> 01:09:34,694
That's enough.

915
01:09:36,305 --> 01:09:40,298
You callJohnny Lovo
at his office at 10
minutes past 2:00, see?

916
01:09:40,376 --> 01:09:43,868
That's 10 minutes
past 2:00.

917
01:09:43,946 --> 01:09:47,609
You say that you callin'
from the country, see?
Uh-huh.

918
01:09:47,683 --> 01:09:50,982
You one of the guys
that took me for a ride.
Uh-huh.

919
01:09:51,053 --> 01:09:54,181
Car got smashed,
and I got away.

920
01:09:54,256 --> 01:09:57,089
The car got smashed,
and I got away!
Yes, yes.

921
01:09:57,159 --> 01:10:00,560
You think it was Johnny?
I don't know, but
we'll find out now.

922
01:10:00,629 --> 01:10:03,189
We'll be there
when Pietro calls.

923
01:10:03,265 --> 01:10:06,132
And if it was Johnny,
he'll stall, won't he?

924
01:10:06,202 --> 01:10:08,466
Sure.
Let's go.

925
01:10:08,537 --> 01:10:10,664
Open the door!

926
01:10:23,686 --> 01:10:25,620
Come on. Let's go.

927
01:10:45,007 --> 01:10:47,942
Hey, Tony, where you been?
What happened to you?

928
01:10:48,010 --> 01:10:51,173
Yeah, look. They spoil
my brand-new suit.

929
01:10:51,247 --> 01:10:54,375
<i>Who? Coppers?</i>
Nah. Monkeys.

930
01:10:54,450 --> 01:10:58,079
Never seen 'em before.
Somebody must've brought 'em in.

931
01:10:58,153 --> 01:11:00,485
How did they get you?

932
01:11:00,556 --> 01:11:05,653
They smashed my bus,
took me for a ride... almost.

933
01:11:05,728 --> 01:11:08,390
That's right.
You left the caf alone.

934
01:11:08,464 --> 01:11:11,228
You oughta know better
than to do that. Where were you?

935
01:11:11,300 --> 01:11:14,235
<i>I thought you always</i>
<i>stuck to Tony.</i>

936
01:11:15,804 --> 01:11:19,069
Well, baby,
I'm glad you got away.
I'd have missed you plenty.

937
01:11:19,141 --> 01:11:22,008
I'll get somebody for this.
I knew you would, Johnny.

938
01:11:22,077 --> 01:11:26,639
<i>[Phone Rings]</i>
That's Poppy. I don't
want to see her tonight.

939
01:11:26,715 --> 01:11:28,808
I'll tell her you ain't in.

940
01:11:28,884 --> 01:11:31,717
Hey, wait a minute.
I'll talk to her.

941
01:11:36,592 --> 01:11:39,527
Hello? Who?

942
01:11:39,595 --> 01:11:42,758
<i>No, there's nobody</i>
<i>here by that name.</i>

943
01:11:42,831 --> 01:11:45,459
<i>What? What?</i>

944
01:11:46,735 --> 01:11:49,568
Oh, ring off.
You got a wrong number.

945
01:11:53,542 --> 01:11:55,476
You better have a drink,
Tony.

946
01:12:02,518 --> 01:12:04,452
You?

947
01:12:15,898 --> 01:12:18,833
<i>[Tony Whistling]</i>

948
01:12:21,136 --> 01:12:23,900
[Continues Whistling]

949
01:13:12,621 --> 01:13:15,146
It's a lie!
I didn't do it!

950
01:13:15,224 --> 01:13:17,624
I wouldn't try anything
on you, Tony! We're pals!

951
01:13:17,693 --> 01:13:19,627
Sure, we're pals.

952
01:13:19,695 --> 01:13:21,686
No, I didn't do it.
You got me wrong.

953
01:13:21,764 --> 01:13:24,699
Listen, Tony, you're
the last guy in the world
I'd try to cross.

954
01:13:24,767 --> 01:13:27,668
<i>You wouldn't do anything to me.</i>
<i>Tony, gimme a chance.</i>

955
01:13:27,736 --> 01:13:30,432
<i>You can have anything I got,</i>
<i>all the dough you want.</i>

956
01:13:30,506 --> 01:13:33,498
Poppy! I'll let you have her.
I give you my word.

957
01:13:33,575 --> 01:13:37,102
You can have Poppy, Tony!
I'll tell her!

958
01:13:37,179 --> 01:13:39,773
The boss!
No!

959
01:13:39,848 --> 01:13:41,873
Let me go away!
Gimme a break!

960
01:13:41,950 --> 01:13:44,885
I ain't never did
anything to anybody!
I never hurt anybody!

961
01:13:44,953 --> 01:13:48,354
Nah, you get somebody else
to do it for ya!

962
01:13:51,560 --> 01:13:53,494
No!

963
01:13:56,365 --> 01:13:59,596
Wait! Don't!
Tony, come back!

964
01:13:59,668 --> 01:14:02,535
<i>Tony.!</i>
<i>[Gunshots]</i>

965
01:14:11,513 --> 01:14:14,414
<i>[Doorbell Buzzing]</i>

966
01:14:18,020 --> 01:14:20,887
<i>[Buzzing Continues]</i>

967
01:14:33,435 --> 01:14:35,369
Oh, Tony.

968
01:14:41,944 --> 01:14:43,969
What's happened?

969
01:14:48,951 --> 01:14:52,614
- Where's Johnny?
- Where do you think?

970
01:14:57,226 --> 01:14:59,160
Go pack your stuff.

971
01:15:38,901 --> 01:15:42,393
Hey, come here.

972
01:15:44,072 --> 01:15:46,006
Lookit there.

973
01:15:46,074 --> 01:15:49,271
<i>Do you remember</i>
<i>what I told ya?</i>

974
01:16:16,204 --> 01:16:18,729
Tony isn't here.
He's out of town.

975
01:16:18,807 --> 01:16:20,798
You're telling me?

976
01:16:22,344 --> 01:16:25,745
Why did you hang up
when I called yesterday?

977
01:16:25,814 --> 01:16:27,748
Too busy.

978
01:16:37,993 --> 01:16:41,053
The one on the end's
kind of cute.

979
01:16:41,129 --> 01:16:43,222
She ain't bad.

980
01:16:46,335 --> 01:16:48,895
I should think you'd want
something more like...

981
01:16:48,971 --> 01:16:50,962
Like what?

982
01:16:52,507 --> 01:16:54,168
Me.

983
01:16:54,242 --> 01:16:57,211
Cut out
that sort of talk.

984
01:16:57,279 --> 01:16:59,713
You're only a kid.

985
01:16:59,781 --> 01:17:02,773
I told you I had
grown-up ideas.

986
01:17:04,553 --> 01:17:08,284
You're like Tony
when you go after
something, hey?

987
01:17:12,628 --> 01:17:14,562
What would Tony say?

988
01:17:14,630 --> 01:17:16,962
He'll be away for a month.

989
01:17:22,671 --> 01:17:25,663
The big fella's
on his way from Florida.

990
01:17:25,741 --> 01:17:29,233
Uh-huh. Well,
he better watch his step.

991
01:17:29,311 --> 01:17:31,472
This town's entirely different
than when he left it.

992
01:17:31,546 --> 01:17:33,810
That new crowd
down at the city hall
is looking for him.

993
01:17:33,882 --> 01:17:37,045
The first crack he makes,
they'll climb all over him.

994
01:17:37,119 --> 01:17:40,714
Hand it to Hap.
Tell him to play it
for what it's worth.

995
01:17:56,972 --> 01:17:59,634
Hey. You stay out here.

996
01:18:13,088 --> 01:18:15,022
Tony.
Where's Cesca?

997
01:18:15,090 --> 01:18:19,754
She got a place of her own.
She say to me, " Shut up.
Mind-a your business."

998
01:18:19,828 --> 01:18:22,353
Well, is she livin' alone?
Yeah.

999
01:18:22,431 --> 01:18:24,695
All-a the time
that what she tell me.

1000
01:18:24,766 --> 01:18:28,099
But one day I follow her.
She meet a man. They go
in the house together.

1001
01:18:28,170 --> 01:18:31,697
I look and I see her name
under the push bell.

1002
01:18:31,773 --> 01:18:35,903
See? See what you do?
Once I have a son,
I have a daughter...

1003
01:18:35,977 --> 01:18:38,741
Shhh.
[Speaking Italian]

1004
01:18:38,814 --> 01:18:40,941
Where is the place
she live?

1005
01:18:41,016 --> 01:18:42,950
236 Central Street.

1006
01:18:46,421 --> 01:18:49,754
What you gonna do?
What you... No, no, Tony!

1007
01:18:49,825 --> 01:18:51,952
Stop!

1008
01:18:58,400 --> 01:19:00,334
Central Street.

1009
01:19:08,810 --> 01:19:11,506
<i>[Jaunty]</i>

1010
01:19:11,580 --> 01:19:15,573
He was goin' downgrade
makin' 90 miles an hour

1011
01:19:15,650 --> 01:19:19,142
When his whistle
broke into a scream
[Whistles]

1012
01:19:19,221 --> 01:19:21,382
And they found him
in the wreck

1013
01:19:21,456 --> 01:19:23,720
With his hands
on the throttle

1014
01:19:23,792 --> 01:19:26,989
Scalded to death
by the steam

1015
01:19:27,062 --> 01:19:30,930
It's a mighty rough road
from Lynchburg to Danville

1016
01:19:30,999 --> 01:19:34,332
And the track's
on the three-mile grade

1017
01:19:34,402 --> 01:19:38,304
It was on this road
that he lost his air brakes

1018
01:19:38,373 --> 01:19:41,536
You can see
what a jump he made

1019
01:19:45,914 --> 01:19:48,747
Hello.
Hello, baby.

1020
01:19:48,817 --> 01:19:52,218
I'm so happy.
You're telling me?

1021
01:19:52,287 --> 01:19:54,221
You do love me,
don't you, Guino?

1022
01:19:54,289 --> 01:19:56,223
You know I do.

1023
01:19:56,291 --> 01:19:59,021
Never stop telling me,
will you?

1024
01:19:59,094 --> 01:20:01,722
I'm not like
all the others, am I?

1025
01:20:01,797 --> 01:20:04,357
You're up there
all by yourself, sweetheart.

1026
01:20:04,432 --> 01:20:06,423
We'll always
be happy, won't we?

1027
01:20:06,501 --> 01:20:09,493
[Whistling]

1028
01:20:15,744 --> 01:20:18,269
<i>[Doorbell Buzzing]</i>

1029
01:20:22,517 --> 01:20:26,886
<i>[Buzzing Continues]</i>

1030
01:20:32,828 --> 01:20:35,319
<i>[Buzzing Continues]</i>

1031
01:20:41,636 --> 01:20:43,570
Hello, Tony.

1032
01:20:47,409 --> 01:20:50,037
Tony, I...

1033
01:20:51,580 --> 01:20:54,071
Tony, don't! Tony!

1034
01:20:54,149 --> 01:20:56,982
<i>[Gunshots]</i>
<i>[Cesca Screams]</i>

1035
01:21:05,093 --> 01:21:08,153
Guino! Guino!

1036
01:21:08,230 --> 01:21:10,790
Guino, speak to me!
Speak to me!

1037
01:21:10,866 --> 01:21:13,733
Guino, say something!
Guino!

1038
01:21:13,802 --> 01:21:17,203
[Sobbing]
Tony, he's my Guino!

1039
01:21:17,272 --> 01:21:20,935
I love him.
We were married yesterday, Tony!

1040
01:21:21,009 --> 01:21:23,534
Really married!

1041
01:21:23,612 --> 01:21:27,639
We were going to surprise you.
Weren't we, Guino?

1042
01:21:27,716 --> 01:21:30,514
Oh, darling, speak to me!
[Sobbing]

1043
01:21:35,457 --> 01:21:37,687
He's dead.

1044
01:21:37,759 --> 01:21:39,693
He's dead.

1045
01:21:41,863 --> 01:21:44,957
He loved me,
really loved me.

1046
01:21:48,270 --> 01:21:50,363
Don't touch me!

1047
01:21:52,941 --> 01:21:55,239
Don't come near me!

1048
01:21:57,012 --> 01:22:00,573
Stay away from me!
You're not my brother!

1049
01:22:02,550 --> 01:22:05,144
Don't you think I know?

1050
01:22:05,220 --> 01:22:07,552
Murderer!

1051
01:22:07,622 --> 01:22:09,954
He kills people!

1052
01:22:10,025 --> 01:22:12,789
He kills everybody!

1053
01:22:12,861 --> 01:22:15,261
He kills everything!

1054
01:22:15,330 --> 01:22:18,390
He's a butcher.
That's what you are.

1055
01:22:18,466 --> 01:22:21,492
You're a butcher!
You're a butcher!

1056
01:22:26,608 --> 01:22:29,475
Drive down to the house.

1057
01:22:31,379 --> 01:22:34,974
<i>[Teletype Tapping]</i>

1058
01:22:43,992 --> 01:22:46,688
[Sirens Wailing]

1059
01:22:52,367 --> 01:22:54,301
Come on, boss.

1060
01:23:04,245 --> 01:23:06,213
[Sirens Wailing]

1061
01:23:06,281 --> 01:23:08,772
Go on, beat it!
Get outta here!

1062
01:23:08,850 --> 01:23:10,875
Come on! Come on!

1063
01:23:48,056 --> 01:23:51,548
<i>[Phone Rings]</i>

1064
01:23:57,966 --> 01:24:00,696
<i>[Ringing Continues]</i>

1065
01:24:04,472 --> 01:24:06,497
[Moans]

1066
01:24:13,815 --> 01:24:15,874
This Mr. Camonte's secre...

1067
01:24:17,185 --> 01:24:20,882
You'll have to speak loud.
I can't hear you.

1068
01:24:25,927 --> 01:24:29,192
It's... It's Poppy, boss.

1069
01:24:30,632 --> 01:24:33,396
I-I got her name.
[Laughs]

1070
01:24:54,656 --> 01:24:58,820
I didn't know.
I didn't know.

